author: COMSOL
description: A cable is a structural member which has stiffness only in its tangential direction, but virtually no bending stiffness. When supported only at its two ends, it deflects under gravitational load forming a curve known as catenary. This example shows how to model components such as cables, wires or strings using the Wire interface.
